UML:TaggedValue.value: This could serve as an execution plan for the Processing Engine. Intention here is to have generic ways of calling the different steps in processing the data. The context will define what methods can be used to get "Elements" from different sources. Also if transformation applies we could possibly create new elements that are derived from the others, but I think we can put the ways of capturing those here, but how and when those would be applied would be upto the Processing Engine. But maybe this is a bad idea, but I do see value in having a basic collector of methods and classes that would dectate how the Processing engine would behave. What driver it uses, what transformations it would apply can all be gathered when parsing over the "Raw Data Description", this will help prepare a context that the processing engine can say oh at this step this is what should happen in a generalized way abstracting it from the details of how to do it. Because how its done can be buried in the objects contained by this context.
